OL,3,CSurviving, not living: The workers
OL,4,Ctaking second jobs in cost-of-living
OL,5,Ccrisis
OL,7,F"If I go on the basic rate of what I'm
OL,8,Fon at the moment, it leaves me enough
OL,9,Fto survive, but not to live.
OL,11,F"I've got a child to look after, and
OL,12,Fwhen you're on your own, and then with
OL,13,Fthe cost-of-living at the moment and
OL,14,Feverything going up, you just got to
OL,15,Fkeep going, to keep grinding it."
OL,17,FHis working boots on, he leaves for
OL,18,Fthe building site at 6.30am.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/20
