OL,5,Ccrisis
OL,7,FWe meet again later that evening after
OL,8,Fhis shift, at the park, with Jacob. He
OL,9,Fadores his son, and his son adores
OL,10,Fhim. As Jamie pushes his boy back and
OL,11,Fforth on the swings, he explains where
OL,12,Fhis money is going.
OL,14,F"It's enough to survive, but not to
OL,15,Flive," Jamie says
OL,17,F"After bills I think I'm left with
OL,18,Fjust shy of #400 pounds a month, but
OL,19,Fwhen you take in consideration fuel
OL,20,Ffor work and a food shop over four
OL,21,Fweeks. It's gone. Nothing is spare."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/20
