OL,3,CSurviving, not living: The workers
OL,4,Ctaking second jobs in cost-of-living
OL,5,Ccrisis
OL,7,F"I have to work... But it's like why
OL,8,Fgo to work when you're paying someone
OL,9,Felse to bring up your children? It
OL,10,Fjust doesn't make sense.
OL,12,F"Yes, you do want to be a good role
OL,13,Fmodel for your children to show them,
OL,14,Flike go out to work every day, but
OL,15,Fthen you're missing out on so much of
OL,16,Ftheir life as well.
OL,18,F"I'm paying all my wages for somebody
OL,19,Felse to look after my child so I could
OL,20,Fbe at home."
