OL,3,CSurviving, not living: The workers
OL,4,Ctaking second jobs in cost-of-living
OL,5,Ccrisis
OL,7,F"The boys are on hourly rates, so if
OL,8,Fthe work's not here for them, then
OL,9,Fthere's no work for them," says 29-
OL,10,Fyear-old production manager Zac Welch.
OL,12,FThe company relies on housebuilding
OL,13,Ffor many of its contracts, but with
OL,14,Fwork dropping off, they're looking at
OL,15,Fthe possibility of having to make
OL,16,Fseven to 10 men redundant.
OL,18,F"It's just to try and stay afloat,"
OL,19,FZac says.
OL,21,FZac also has his own family to support.
